The '''FIBA Women's World Ranking''' is the [[FIBA]]'s rankings of national women's [[basketball]] teams. FIBA ranks women's national teams in both senior and junior competitions. It also publishes combined rankings for all competitions involving both sexes.
==Calculation== FIBA still uses the competition-based system to determine its women's rankings. As noted above, this system was also used to determine men's rankings prior to 2017. FIBA has announced that it will introduce a game-based ranking procedure similar to that currently used for men's rankings in the indeterminate future.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/documents/rankingmen/faq |title=FIBA World Ranking Men, presented by Nike – Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) |publisher=FIBA |accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref>
===Events' weights=== FIBA uses a [[weighted arithmetic mean]] to determine the statistical weight of each of the tournaments. Each event is assigned point weight that is based partly on how competitive the tournament is and partly on which national teams are participating:<ref name="how">[http://www.fiba.com/pages/eng/fc/even/rank/p/openNodeIDs/998/selNodeID/998/howItWork.html FIBA.com: How it works]</ref> {|class="wikitable" |- !Number !!width=550px|Event !! Weight |- | 2 || [[FIBA Women's Basketball World Cup]] || 5 |- | 2 || [[Basketball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic basketball tournaments]] || 5 |- | 4 || [[AfroBasket Women]] || 0.2 |- | 4 || [[FIBA Women's AmeriCup]] || 0.8 |- | 4 || [[FIBA Asia Women's Cup]] || 0.3 |- | 4 || [[EuroBasket Women]] || 1 |- | 4 || [[FIBA Oceania Women's Championship]] || 0.1 |}
===Competition ranking points=== [[File:FIFA World Rankings for Women.png|thumb|300px|Map of FIBA World Ranking for women]] As opposed to [[Association football|football]] tournaments, teams still have to go through a series of consolation and classification rounds even if they've been eliminated from title contention, so that a complete ranking of the teams will be possible.<ref name="how"/> {|class="wikitable" |- !width=200px|Competition rank !! Points |- |align=left| Gold medal (1st) ||align=right|50 |- |align=left| Silver medal (2nd) ||align=right|40 |- |align=left| Bronze medal (3rd) ||align=right|30 |- |align=left| 4th ||align=right|15 |- |align=left| 5th ||align=right|14 |- |align=left| 6th ||align=right|13 |- |align=left| 7th ||align=right|12 |- |align=left| 8th ||align=right|11 |- |align=left| 9th ||align=right|10 |- |align=left| 10th ||align=right|9 |- |align=left| 11th ||align=right|8 |- |align=left| 12th ||align=right|7 |- |align=left| 13th ||align=right|6 |- |align=left| 14th ||align=right|5 |- |align=left| 15th ||align=right|4 |- |align=left| 16th ||align=right|3 |- |align=left| 17th ||align=right|2 |- |align=left| 18th and below ||align=right|1 |}
